# Pass 0135 Ledger - Wide Research Substrate and Bio/Med/Robotics Nomenclature Map

Date: 2026-07-02

## Objective

This pass answers the broadened research direction: source from publishing archives, preprint servers, college and public research databases, and cross-domain source substrates without narrowing the mission to one field. The concrete artifact is a first wide substrate map, with biology, medicine, and robotics as the initial topical slice and a broader expansion queue for mathematics, physics, materials, chemistry, climate/energy, security, finance, education, governance/law, neuroscience, and economics.

The pass does not claim a discovery, law, theorem solution, clinical result, robot safety result, or market uniqueness fact. It creates a receipt-backed map for where future proof packets should pull evidence and how equivalent ideas appear under different names across fields.

